<TITLE> BDR rebels want to see PM, general pardon </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka Feb 25 (bdnews24.com)  Rebel BDR personnel have said they need to speak to the prime minister and her cabinet members to end the standoff at the BDR Headquarters where gunshots erupted Wednesday morning. She will also have to declare general amnesty for the rebels and meet their demands. "Otherwise, we will not stop the 'war'," a member told a private TV station. Claiming to be a representative of one "Nayek Shahid", a man speaking behind a window wearing helmet, his face covered, said, "The gate no. 3 is open to the prime minister and members of the cabinet." A BDR rebel announced at around 3:00 pm through BanglaVision that they would talk to the government delegates if they went up to the third gate of the BDR HQ. bdnew
